Okay, so this commit changes `gfp_t` from an `unsigned int __bitwise` to an `unsigned long __bitwise`. The goal is to allow 64-bit GFP flags on 64-bit systems, which makes sense given that we're running out of bits. The commit updates some `printk` formats and addresses a change in `lib/test_lockup.c` concerning `module_param_unsafe`.

