But wait, is this change really that problematic? On 32-bit systems, `unsigned long` remains 32-bit, so `gfp_t`'s size stays the same. The change only affects 64-bit systems. So it might be ok after all.

Now, tracepoints. If tracepoints output `gfp_t`, they might use `__print_flags`, which may have size expectations. Additionally, while `gfp_to_alloc_flags` returns an `unsigned int`, that should be fine.

