ake.rst-103-could not be started. A negative errno guarantees the callback function\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-104-@ta_done will not be invoked on this socket.\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-105-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-106-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-107-To initiate a client-side TLS handshake with a pre-shared key, use:\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-108-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-109-.. code-block:: c\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-110-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst:111:  ret = tls_client_hello_psk(args, gfp_flags);\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-112-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-113-However, in this case, the consumer fills in the @ta_my_peerids array\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-114-with serial numbers of keys containing the peer identities it wishes\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-115-to offer, and the @ta_num_peerids field with the number of array\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-116-entries it has filled in. The other fields are filled in as above.\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-117-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-118-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-119-To initiate an anonymous client-side TLS handshake use:\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-120-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-121-.. code-block:: c\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-122-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst:123:  ret = tls_client_hello_anon(args, gfp_flags);\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-124-\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-125-The handshake agent presents no peer identity information to the remote\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-126-during this type of handshake. Only server authentication (ie the client\nDocumentation/networking/tls-handshake.rst-127-verifies the server's identity) is per